I could do it all.

38:18.666 --> 38:21.291
Because I was so determined
to make today perfect

38:21.291 --> 38:23.000
that I just got lost
in the details,

38:23.000 --> 38:25.416
and I refused to respect
anyone else's opinion

38:25.416 --> 38:27.208
other than my own?

38:27.208 --> 38:28.750
- And?

38:28.750 --> 38:30.416
- And I was a total, insane,
control freak.

38:30.416 --> 38:33.041
- Bingo. All right,
I will work my magic,

38:33.041 --> 38:34.583
but on one condition:

38:34.583 --> 38:36.083
you do everything I tell you,
no questions asked.

38:36.083 --> 38:38.041
- I promise.
- Good.

38:38.041 --> 38:39.375
All right.
Now, let's get up on stage.

38:39.375 --> 38:41.708
Andrea: (Snorts) Is that weird?

38:41.708 --> 38:43.750
- If this book is your life
then... let's hear it.

38:46.416 --> 38:48.333
- 'Kay.
- Whoa. That domestic
discipline thing,

38:48.333 --> 38:51.125
is there a website?
- (Squeal of urgency)
Oh, come on.

38:51.125 --> 38:53.250
- The life of a single girl,
huh, Katie? Oh.

38:54.833 --> 38:56.625
- And on that charming note,
scene.

38:56.625 --> 38:59.416
What you just witnessed
is every man's nightmare.

38:59.416 --> 39:01.708
An over-sexed, slightly
desperate young woman--

39:01.708 --> 39:05.500
- Excuse me?
- Willing to suffer date
after soul-crushing date

39:05.500 --> 39:07.083
just to find the one.

39:07.083 --> 39:09.458
She is a victim of every single
30-something dating book

39:09.458 --> 39:11.125
that's ever been written.

39:11.125 --> 39:12.666
Until now.

39:12.666 --> 39:15.208
Because "The None"
is none of that.

39:15.208 --> 39:17.416
The "The None" is something new,

39:17.416 --> 39:19.000
something groundbreaking.

39:19.000 --> 39:21.416
Something... Erica Strange.

39:21.416 --> 39:23.208
(Applause)

39:26.041 --> 39:28.166
- Who do you think you are?
- Your destiny.

39:28.166 --> 39:31.125
You free tonight?
- No.

39:31.125 --> 39:32.875
Maybe I could be.
- Hmm.

39:36.416 --> 39:39.458
- Well, I hope you enjoyed
our little pre-show,

39:39.458 --> 39:42.083
but Erica here is actually the
inspiration for my new book.

39:44.208 --> 39:46.916
An incredible woman
who deserves an incredible man,

39:48.541 --> 39:50.625
but who has so far been
unlucky in love.

39:50.625 --> 39:53.666
- Not that I haven't had my fair
share of opportunities though.

39:53.666 --> 39:56.666
- Why do you think
you're still single?

39:56.666 --> 39:58.500
- You know what? It's this...

39:58.500 --> 40:01.250
rabid desire, you know,
to find "the one."

40:01.250 --> 40:03.416
It-it sounds like
it's about the guy,

40:03.416 --> 40:05.666
but really it's about the girl.

40:05.666 --> 40:08.083
- How do you mean?

40:08.083 --> 40:10.125
- Well, it's the expectations
we have, you know?

40:10.125 --> 40:12.125
It cuts the male right out
of the equation

40:12.125 --> 40:16.375
because any good relationship,
it's about both people.

40:16.375 --> 40:18.416
Katie: You mean you've spent
so many years

40:18.416 --> 40:19.958
going after what you want,

40:19.958 --> 40:22.125
that you forgot that half
of the relationship

40:22.125 --> 40:23.958
is actually in somebody
else's hands.

40:23.958 --> 40:25.541
- Yeah. Exactly, exactly.

40:25.541 --> 40:27.541
'Cause any true relationship,
it's never just about yourself,

40:29.208 --> 40:32.583
so... so if you can stop
looking at it like that

40:32.583 --> 40:35.166
and put aside your desire
to find the perfect man,

40:38.625 --> 40:40.500
you might just find the man
that's perfect for you.

40:43.208 --> 40:44.833
(Applause)

40:46.333 --> 40:47.916
- Oh. Thanks, Katie.

40:52.041 --> 40:53.458
- Okay, so those go
in the records room

40:53.458 --> 40:55.041
and if it's locked,
Brent has the key.

40:55.041 --> 40:57.625
- Okay. Look, I'm sorry if I...

40:57.625 --> 41:00.458
- Oh, Meeri, don't apologize
for anything.

41:00.458 --> 41:03.083
You did a great job today,
really. So thank you.

41:03.083 --> 41:04.916
- (Flattered gasp) Okay.

41:09.166 --> 41:10.541
Julianne: (Clears throat)

41:10.541 --> 41:11.875
Look down.

41:13.375 --> 41:16.333
Look down.

41:16.333 --> 41:19.625
- Oh my God.
- No guff.

41:19.625 --> 41:21.583
It wasn't too long ago
you were just a...

41:21.583 --> 41:24.250
a poorly-dressed girl
past her prime

41:24.250 --> 41:26.208
with a penchant for flip-flops.

41:26.208 --> 41:28.750
It's amazing what a few months
can do.

41:28.750 --> 41:30.791
- Is this for real?
Are you serious?

41:30.791 --> 41:33.250
- (Half laughs) I may be tough,
but I'm not unfair.

41:35.458 --> 41:38.125
You proved yourself today.
- Thank you.

41:38.125 --> 41:39.666
Uh, but, I mean,
I had a lot of help.

41:39.666 --> 41:41.625
Brent, of course,
was invaluable,

41:41.625 --> 41:43.541
and Meeri, she's--

41:43.541 --> 41:45.458
- It was a team effort
blah-blah-blah-blah-blah.

41:45.458 --> 41:47.625
You were the one in charge,
so enjoy it.

41:49.250 --> 41:51.166
Oh, we're gonna need
to find a new Erica.

41:51.166 --> 41:54.083
One who actually knows
how to brew a latte.

41:54.083 --> 41:55.416
- Definitely.

41:57.166 --> 41:59.041
- High-five. (Hands clap)

41:59.041 --> 42:01.458
- Thank you.

42:01.458 --> 42:03.750
There comes a day
when we suddenly realize

42:03.750 --> 42:05.375
that the control we seek

42:05.375 --> 42:09.583
will forever remain
just outside our grasp.

42:09.583 --> 42:11.625
For some,
it's a terrifying discovery.

42:14.458 --> 42:17.000
While for others,
it's strangely liberating.

42:18.583 --> 42:20.041
If the only person
I can control is me,

42:21.708 --> 42:23.791
that means I'm off the hook
for the other six billion souls

42:23.791 --> 42:26.000
making their way
in this crazy world.

42:28.375 --> 42:29.666
- Thank you. Mm-hmm.

42:31.166 --> 42:32.500
(Knock at the door)

42:32.500 --> 42:34.083
- Coming!

42:37.666 --> 42:40.666
- Hey.
- Hey. What happened
to knocking on my wall?

42:40.666 --> 42:42.541
- Can I come in?
- Where's Claire?

42:42.541 --> 42:45.000
- Montreal. Can I come in?

42:47.750 --> 42:49.375
(Door creaks shut)

42:51.000 --> 42:53.166
- What you said to me,
I-I didn't like it, Erica.

42:53.166 --> 42:54.666
- Well, I didn't like saying it.

42:54.666 --> 42:57.083
- But you did and...
and you weren't wrong.

42:59.708 --> 43:02.208
I was paralyzed, in a way.

43:02.208 --> 43:04.250
Claire held all the cards and...

43:04.250 --> 43:07.416
when she wanted me back, I...
- Yeah, you went. I know.

43:07.416 --> 43:09.291
- But I didn't, not really,
because you were right.

43:11.166 --> 43:14.041
If I really wanted her,
I'd be in Montreal.

43:15.666 --> 43:18.583
I wouldn't be here... with you.

43:18.583 --> 43:20.708
♪ Every little thing I do ♪

43:22.958 --> 43:25.291
♪ Trickles down
and lands on you ♪

43:27.333 --> 43:29.625
♪ When I see your face
so bright ♪

43:31.375 --> 43:32.791
♪ Makes me wanna do... ♪

43:32.791 --> 43:34.875
- What took you so long?!

43:34.875 --> 43:37.333
♪ Every little thing right... ♪
